entry.title: ARCVM: Don't use timed switches when suspending ARC
entry.content:
Whenever ARCVM goes into suspend because the ChromeBook physical

display is turned off, it must turn off the delayed-doze timer

mechanism, to make sure the state stays synced.

This is done by observing all changes in the display power

observer, as opposed to only those which change overall state.

entry.title: Try to fix compositor creation to commit/swap UMAs
entry.content:
In crrev.com/c/5086331 we added metrics to measure how often it

is that compositor creation for a new RenderWidgetHost created for

a navigation happened before the navigation commits or swaps in the

RenderFrameHost, and how long is the delta in time between the events.



UMA shows confusing results (see go/compositorcreationtocommit-uma),

where in a rather significant amount of navigations,

CompositorCreationToCommit/SwapRFH takes longer than 180k ms (3 mins),

implying that the compositor creation happens long before the commit

or RFH swap.



Meanwhile, Navigation.PendingCommit.Duration says the duration from

Commit to DidCommit (which should be slightly lower than Commit to

RFH swap) takes way less than that. Similarly Navigation.TimeToReadyToCommit2 says the duration from navigation

start to Commit (which should be strictly longer than

CompositorCreationToCommit) also takes way less than that.



Since there seems to be a bug in recording the metric, this CL

tries to fix this by:

- Making sure we only record the metrics on navigations that

create a new RenderWidgetHost, by checking that the navigation

is committing a new pending commit RenderFrameHost

- Making sure the timestamp for compositor creation for a navigation

won't be mixed with another navigation, by resetting the timestamps

after we record the metrics.

- Also recording the delta when the compositor creation happens

after the commit/swap RFH, to see if that case also has confusing

data.



OBSOLETE_HISTOGRAMS=Navigation.CompositorCreationTo{Stage} is replaced by Navigation.CompositorCreationTo{Stage}2

OBSOLETE_HISTOGRAMS=Navigation.CompositorRequestedBefore{Stage} is replaced by Navigation.CompositorRequestedBefore{Stage}2

the flakiness due to the race from async last active browser

update.

entry.content:
Currently, ExtractData can return WebCustomData without checking the

requested MIME type when one is provided. This is problematic if the

from Lacros WebUI tabstrip, the provider also provides data with

kMimeTypeDataTransferEndpoint in addition to kMimeTypeWebCustomData.



This CL changes ExtractData to return WebCustomData only if the

requested MIME type matches kMimeTypeWebCustomData.

entry.title: Refactor MP4 muxer to include a separate class for fragment construction.
entry.content:
Previously, the code was somewhat complex, particularly in the

areas of fragment creation and track management. This complexity

arose because tracks could be dynamically added to newly created

fragments, requiring dynamic handling.



The modifications have moved the logic for managing tracks

and their fragments to a separate class, Mp4MuxerDelegateFragment.

This class uses static track indices, which are corrected before writing.



Overall, the process of fragment creation and box writing is

now more transparent in the Mp4MuxerDelegate. Meanwhile,

the Mp4MuxerDelegateFragment is responsible for storing

incoming samples with the correct track information and returning

them upon request. This makes the code clearer and easier to understand.



Additional modifications include the introduction of a

static timestamp for the last item of each fragment, simplifying the process.

Furthermore, an empty fragment is now added if the file

contains both video and audio tracks, but a specific

fragment lacks one of these tracks due to system issues.

entry.title: [CrOS Bluetooth] Use HidPreservingBluetoothStateController in QS
entry.content:
This CL uses newly added HidPreserving API in Bluetooth Quick Settings

views. It ensures that the user does not unknowingly disable Bluetooth

while only having HID devices connected from Quick settings. It adds

a new service GetHidPreservingBluetoothStateControllerService that would

be used as the entry point for HidPreservingBluetoothController Mojo

API.



Note:

GetHidPreservingBluetoothStateControllerService was added to

ash/system/bluetooth/hid_preserving_controller/ folder because adding

this to ash/public/ would create a circular dependency as HidPreservingBluetoothController also depends on a service in

a/p/cpp.



Fixed: b/324302529

entry.title: Resolve races between `PRE_UNSUBSCRIBE` and organic actions.
entry.content:
After the user taps the `PRE_UNSUBSCRIBE` action on a notification, we

need to complete native startup before we can replace the tapped

notification with the "provisionally unsubscribed" service notification.



In this time window, the user might have tapped the content or a

developer-provided action button. Given the strong indication the user

may want to stop getting these notifications, resolve this conflict by

silently discarding the action.



Furthermore, if the developer closes the notification the user tapped on

while the service notification is showing in its stead, do not let the

service notification it be canceled. The organic notification is at this

point already deleted from the `NotificationDatabase` in response to it

being closed by the developer. If the user clicks `UNDO_UNSUBSCRIBE`, we

will not restore the cancelled notification.
